{"id":8485,"date":"2018-11-05T14:38:50","date_gmt":"2018-11-05T14:38:50","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/3.121.174.137\/?p=8485"},"modified":"2022-08-12T10:07:17","modified_gmt":"2022-08-12T10:07:17","slug":"casual-connect-belgrade-2018","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/casual-connect-belgrade-2018\/","title":{"rendered":"Casual Connect Belgrade 2018"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-post\" data-elementor-id=\"8485\" class=\"elementor elementor-8485\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-1bd83755 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"1bd83755\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-21d01e72\" data-id=\"21d01e72\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-180dc71b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"180dc71b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><!-- wp:heading --><\/p>\n<h2>wappier\u00a0does #CCBelgrade!\u00a0\u2708\ufe0f<\/h2>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Casual Connect this October 2018 in Belgrade was just awesome! <a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/in\/tedverani\">Ted Verani<\/a>,\u00a0wappier&#8217;s VP of Business Development, was there\u00a0to meet old and new industry folks and moderate a #NotToBeMissed panel with:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bryan Mashinter, VP of Live Games @ Wooga<\/li>\n<li>Chris O&#8217;Kelly, Head of Publishing @ Huuuge<\/li>\n<li>Jure Rasic, Head of Product @ NANOBIT<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Panel title: <strong>&#8220;Designing Games for Optimal IAP&#8221;<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>What did we talk about? While the vast majority of mobile game revenue is earned through in-app purchases, designing games for optimal IAP remains a major challenge, requiring deep knowledge of UX design, virtual economy tuning, pricing economics, and many other disciplines. Featuring experts across these fields, this panel will give attendees concrete and proven advice for designing free-to-play, IAP-driven mobile games which consistently drive IAPs without alienating the player base.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Here is a sneak peek:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:image {\"id\":1377,\"align\":\"center\"} --><\/p>\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img class=\"wp-image-1377\" src=\"https:\/\/kb.wappier.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/IMG_0067-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<figcaption>Good-looking crowd ready to roll!<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<p><!-- \/wp:image --><!-- wp:core-embed\/youtube {\"url\":\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=ZgZCAZosbfA\\u0026feature=youtu.be\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} --><\/p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=ZgZCAZosbfA&amp;feature=youtu.be<\/div>\n<figcaption>Watch our panel session @ Casual Connect Belgrade 2018!<\/figcaption>\n<\/figure>\n<p><!-- \/wp:core-embed\/youtube --><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><b>Next stop:<\/b>\u00a0Dev.Play Conference in Bucharest powered by Romanian Game Developers Association &#8211; RGDA!\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>Ping us at <a href=\"mailto:events@wappier.com\">events@wappier.com<\/a> if you wanna meet while there.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>wappier\u00a0does #CCBelgrade!\u00a0\u2708\ufe0f Casual Connect this October 2018 in Belgrade was just awesome! Ted Verani,\u00a0wappier&#8217;s VP of Business Development, was there\u00a0to meet old and new industry folks and moderate a #NotToBeMissed panel with: Bryan Mashinter, VP of Live Games @ Wooga Chris O&#8217;Kelly, Head of Publishing @ Huuuge Jure Rasic, Head of Product @ NANOBIT Panel [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":15,"featured_media":13737,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"om_disable_all_campaigns":false},"categories":[33,81],"tags":[41,40,42,43,37],"acf":[],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8485"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/15"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=8485"}],"version-history":[{"count":13,"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8485\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":29350,"href":"https:\/\/wappier.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8485\/revisions\/29350"}],"wp:featuredmedia